    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="379"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d379">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/7002: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-30T19:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 30, 1937—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 30—3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1679. In connection with the radio broadcast by the Franco government yesterday
                    announcing a blockade of the Spanish coasts, we understand from the Ministry of
                    Marine that the French Consul General at San Sebastian notified the French
                    Government that he had been advised by the Franco government that there no
                    longer existed any free access to Valencia and Barcelona, and that it was no
                    longer safe for ships to pass along the east Spanish coast, even within the
                    3–mile limit.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
